229: // SeriesLifecycleCallback specifies a list of callbacks that will be called during a lifecycle of a series.
230: // It is always a no-op in Prometheus and mainly meant for external users who import TSDB.
231: // All the callbacks should be safe to be called concurrently.
232: // It is up to the user to implement soft or hard consistency by making the callbacks
233: // atomic or non-atomic. Atomic callbacks can cause degradation performance.
234: type SeriesLifecycleCallback interface {
235: 	// PreCreation is called before creating a series to indicate if the series can be created.
236: 	// A non nil error means the series should not be created.
237: 	PreCreation(labels.Labels) error
238: 	// PostCreation is called after creating a series to indicate a creation of series.
239: 	PostCreation(labels.Labels)
240: 	// PostDeletion is called after deletion of series.
241: 	PostDeletion(map[chunks.HeadSeriesRef]labels.Labels)
242: }
